Sentencas: Reformed fuel gases utilized in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) contain significant amounts of carbon in the form of CO and CO2.
Titulo: Carburisation of interconnect materials in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Alloys, Such as ferritic stainless steels, which are utilized as interconnect materials in intermediate temperature SOFCs may, therefore, be susceptible to carburisation.
Titulo: Carburisation of interconnect materials in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Long-term exposure of ferritic stainless steel, with and without a nickel protective layer, to simulated carbon-containing fuel gas environments has been Studied.
Titulo: Carburisation of interconnect materials in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Optical and electron microscopy (both SEM and TEM) techniques were utilized to characterize the microstructures prior to and after carburising.
Titulo: Carburisation of interconnect materials in solid oxide fuel cells
